</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Hopes of a breakthrough on Cyprus appeared to recede yesterday with Turkey's
parliament postponing today's debate on United Nations' confidence building
measures to end the 20-year division of the island. The rescheduling of the
debate to Tuesday is a snub to prime minister Mrs Tansu Ciller, who has
